Vice President Biden met with former Israeli President Shimon Peres at the Peres Center for Peace in Tel Aviv. They discussed various regional issues and condemned the recent attack in Jaffa, expressing condolences to the family of the American citizen who was killed and wishing a quick recovery for the wounded. They also discussed enhancing collaboration between the US and Israel in cancer research. After the meeting, they briefly interacted with Israeli and Palestinian girls involved in the Peres Center's Girls Football program, which aims to foster friendship and understanding through sports.